{
  "texts": [
    "For AI systems, the notion of a MinSet presents an interesting perspective.",
    "While such a set could theoretically offer a condensed yet comprehensive lexicon for a language model, the challenge remains that AI, unlike children, cannot ground these words through direct sensorimotor experiences.",
    "This limitation highlights the gap between human language acquisition and AI language processing.",
    "SH: There is no doubt that a lot more sensorimotor grounding is done, and is needed, than the formal minimum in terms of dictionary MinSets.",
    "Not only is redundancy needed for robustness, but lots of categories need to be learned even before they are named."
  ]
}